COVID-19 Visualizations

Created by Jill E. Thomley

Monday, April 20, 2020 @ 09:15 PM

library(tidyverse)
library(scales)

Data Sources

  • https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/cases-updates/cases-in-us.html
  • https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus-interactive/index.html
  • https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2020/us/coronavirus-stay-at-home-order.html
stateFIPS <- read_csv("FIPS50.csv")

data <- read_csv("US_MAP_DATA_20200417.csv", skip = 1) %>% 
  right_join(stateFIPS) %>% 
  mutate(Mortality = Deaths/Cases)

dataNC <- data %>% 
  filter(ABBR == "NC")

Total Number of Confirmed Cases

mediancases <- data %>% 
  summarize(rate = median(Cases)) %>% 
  pull()

ggplot(data, aes(x = reorder(Name, Cases), 
                 y = Cases, 
                 color = Cases > mediancases,
                 fill = Cases > mediancases)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", width = 0.1) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_point(dataNC, 
             mapping = aes(x = Name, y = Cases), 
             color = "#103E5D", 
             size = 3) +
  geom_label(dataNC, 
             mapping = aes(label = Name, x = Name, y = Cases),
             hjust = 0, 
             nudge_y = 10000, 
             color = "white", 
             fill = "#103E5D") +
  annotate(geom = "rect", 
           xmin = 46.5, 
           xmax = 51.5,
           ymin = -Inf,
           ymax = Inf,
           fill = "#B41F78",
           alpha = 0.15) +
  annotate(geom = "rect", 
           xmin = 41.5, 
           xmax = 46.5,
           ymin = -Inf,
           ymax = Inf,
           fill = "#B41F78",
           alpha = 0.075) +
  annotate(geom = "rect", 
           xmin = 0.5, 
           xmax = 5.5,
           ymin = -Inf,
           ymax = Inf,
           fill = "#4C7314",
           alpha = 0.15) +
  annotate(geom = "rect", 
           xmin = 5.5, 
           xmax = 10.5,
           ymin = -Inf,
           ymax = Inf,
           fill = "#4C7314",
           alpha = 0.075) +
  scale_y_continuous(label = comma, breaks = seq(0, 300000, 25000)) +
  labs(title = "Total Number of Confirmed COVID-19 Cases",
       subtitle = paste("CDC data as of April 17 @5:48pm, median cases =", mediancases),
       x = NULL, 
       y = "number of confirmed cases",
       caption = "source: https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus-interactive/index.html") +
  coord_flip() +
  theme_linedraw() +
  theme(legend.position = "none",
        axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1),
        axis.title.x = element_text(size = 12)) +
  scale_color_brewer(palette = "Paired")

Mortality Rate by State

nationalrate <- data %>%
  summarize(rate = sum(Deaths)/sum(Cases)) %>% 
  pull(rate)

ggplot(data, aes(x = reorder(Name, Mortality), 
                 y = Mortality, 
                 color = Mortality > nationalrate,
                 fill = Mortality > nationalrate)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", 
           width = 0.1) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_point(dataNC, 
             mapping = aes(x = Name, y = Mortality), 
             color = "#103E5D", 
             size = 3) +
  geom_label(dataNC, 
             mapping = aes(label = Name, x = Name, y = Mortality),
             hjust = 0, 
             nudge_y = 0.004, 
             color = "white", 
             fill = "#103E5D") +
  annotate(geom = "rect", 
           xmin = 46.5, 
           xmax = 51.5,
           ymin = -Inf,
           ymax = Inf,
           fill = "#B41F78",
           alpha = 0.15) +
  annotate(geom = "rect", 
           xmin = 41.5, 
           xmax = 46.5,
           ymin = -Inf,
           ymax = Inf,
           fill = "#B41F78",
           alpha = 0.075) +
  annotate(geom = "rect", 
           xmin = 0.5, 
           xmax = 5.5,
           ymin = -Inf,
           ymax = Inf,
           fill = "#4C7314",
           alpha = 0.15) +
  annotate(geom = "rect", 
           xmin = 5.5, 
           xmax = 10.5,
           ymin = -Inf,
           ymax = Inf,
           fill = "#4C7314",
           alpha = 0.075) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = nationalrate, 
             color = "#B41F78", 
             linetype = "dashed") +
  scale_y_continuous(breaks = seq(0, .10, .01)) +
  labs(title = "COVID-19 Mortality Rate (Deaths/Cases)",
       subtitle = paste("CDC data as of April 17 @5:48pm, national rate = ", 
                        100*round(nationalrate, 4), 
                        "%", 
                        sep = ""),
       x = NULL, 
       y = "mortality rate",
       caption = "source: https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus-interactive/index.html") +
  coord_flip() +
  theme_linedraw() +
  theme(legend.position = "none",
        axis.title.x = element_text(size = 12)) +
  scale_color_brewer(palette = "Paired")
